              {
                "dsDescriptionValue": {
                  "typeName": "dsDescriptionValue",
                  "typeClass": "primitive",
                  "multiple": false,
                  "value": "A tidy, documented, reproducible dataset of Colorado daily climate-station observations — temperature (max/mean/min), precipitation, snowfall / snow depth / snow water equivalent, pan evaporation, solar radiation, vapor pressure, and wind run (twelve measurement types) — liberated from the Colorado DWR/CDSS Climate Station Time Series (day) API into a single long-format CSV: one row per (source, site_id, datetime, variable). One API federates five observing networks (NOAA COOP/GHCN, CoCoRaHS, NRCS/SNOTEL, CoAgMet, NCWCD); units are harmonized PER measurement type (degF, in, mJ/m^2, kPa, km), not globally. Each station carries its full period of record. The committed seed is a 40-station active cross-section, expandable to the full CDSS catalog (~4,962 distinct stations). Part of the Colorado Environmental Data Hub (CUPIDS Lab); implements issue #44. Note: an apiKey is effectively required (anonymous pulls hit a daily-data limit). Snow variables (SnowSWE/SnowDepth) overlap NRCS SNOTEL — build the site crosswalk before treating CDSS and NRCS values for the same physical site as independent. Each extract carries per-source provenance (source URL, retrieval time, SHA-256, license). Regenerated and re-audited monthly from the CDSS API; see the repository for the re-runnable pipeline."
                }
              }
            ]
          },
